title.narrative: PUBLIC ENGATEMENT

description.narrative: The public across the MENA region, including adolescents, are increasingly engaged in promoting positive change for children., which contributes to Adolescent Empowerment, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Equitable Access To Quality Education, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Skills Development. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: UNICEF demonstrates enhanced evidence-informed leadership and broadened partnerships to promote child rights and wellbeing across MENA.

description.narrative: In 2021, the Middle East and North Africa Regional Office (MENARO) continued to focus on the impact of coronavirus (COVID-19) and armed conflict on children’s lives and well-being. MENARO published nearly 100statements, news notes and press releases, as well as close to 100 media interviews, on international and regional channels in the Middle East and North Africa (MENA). It actedas an essential and trustworthy source of information for the public, increasingly focusing on vaccines, vaccine hesitancy and children’s rights.MENARO’s engagement continued to grow with the expansion of its audience to over 1 million followers across several platforms.; | Status:Met | As-of Date:23/03/2022
